   <concept id="FAR_9_406_4" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">9.406-4</ph> Period of debarment.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d589e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d589e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e15">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Debarment shall
be for a period commensurate with the seriousness of the cause(s).
Generally, debarment should not exceed 3 years, except that-</p>
                     <ol id="d589e33" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e21">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Debarment for violation of the provisions of <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?path=/prelim@title41/subtitle4/chapter81&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. chapter 81</xref>, Drug-Free Workplace (see 
                                 <xref href="26.505.dita#FAR_26_505"
                                    base="i1094571"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">26.505</xref>) may be for a period not to exceed 5 years;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e32">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Debarments
under <xref href="9.406-2.dita#FAR_9_406_2"
                                    base="i1115334"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">9.406-2</xref>(b)(2) shall be
for 1 year unless extended pursuant to paragraph (b) of this section;
and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e40">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              Debarments under <xref href="9.406-2.dita#FAR_9_406_2"
                                    base="i1115334"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">9.406-2</xref>(b)(1)(vii) shall
be for a period of not less than 2 years, inclusive of any suspension period,
if suspension precedes a debarment (see paragraph (a)(2) of this
section).
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e48">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> If suspension
precedes a debarment, the suspension period shall be considered
in determining the debarment period.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e53">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  The suspending and debarring official may extend the debarment for an additional period, if that official determines that an extension is necessary to protect the Government’s interest. However, a debarment may not be extended solely on the basis of the facts and circumstances upon which the initial debarment action was based. Debarments under <xref href="9.406-2.dita#FAR_9_406_2"
                        base="i1115334"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.406-2</xref>(b)(2) may be extended for additional periods of one year if the Secretary of Homeland Security or the Attorney General determines that the contractor continues to be in violation of the employment provisions of the Immigration and Nationality Act. If debarment for an additional period is determined to be necessary, the procedures of <xref href="9.406-3.dita#FAR_9_406_3"
                        base="i1115383"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.406-3</xref> shall be followed to extend the debarment.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e64">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  The suspending and debarring official may reduce the period or extent of debarment, upon the contractor’s request, supported by documentation, for reasons such as-</p>
               <ol id="d589e95" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e70">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Newly
discovered material evidence;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e75">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Reversal
of the conviction or civil judgment upon which the debarment was
based;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e80">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Bona fide
change in ownership or management;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e85">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Elimination
of other causes for which the debarment was imposed; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d616e90">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph> Other reasons the the suspending and debarring official deems appropriate.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
